'''Level 365''', more known as "Is this a dream?" or "Lobotomy Lane," is the 366th level of [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]].

==Description==
{{Blurimage|align=right|file=I am worried.jpg|caption=<big>I am worried. I am scared.</big>

<small>The only known image of the house.</small>}}
'''Level 365''' is a lonesome house in a flat field of grass that expands four kilometers in every direction, surrounded by a large wall lined with a moving sky wallpaper set in permanent daytime. The house itself is an average 1990s-2000s suburban home made of white concrete, with a slate roof, a garage, and additional amenities. The sun suffers from several anomalies, including color and subtle shape changes. Wanderers report hearing sounds like bird chirps, rustling leaves, and cars, even though there is nothing present to produce these noises.

'''Level 365''' suffers from a modification of the [[Phenomenon 15|Alone]] phenomenon, in which a wanderer will be immediately expelled from the level when another arrives.{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Sky hand.jpg|caption=<big>I don't want to go.</big>
<small>A recovered image of the Sky Hand. Photographer unknown.</small>|hovertext=I don't want to leave.|width=280px}}

<br>The main hazard of '''Level 365''' is the Sky Hand. It is not an entity, as it does not seem to have the common traits of one. It is a giant white hand that descends from the sky when wanderers stay on the level for too long. Once it appears, the wanderer should hide from it to avoid getting caught. Signs of the Hand appearing include clouds disappearing or the Hand itself being barely visible, although it remains unmoving. After being captured by the Sky Hand, wanderers are taken to an unknown location. No one has returned, so the outcome cannot be confirmed.

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Don't leave .jpg|caption=<big>Don't you want to know?</big>

<small>The only widely available image of the gate.</small>|hovertext=Don't leave.|width=280px}}

In the boundaries of the level, there is a door-esque hole in the skybox, through which wanderers can pass. There is a dirt pathway that leads to this entrance, surrounded by a motionless cloud in the wallpaper. The level becomes unstable as wanderers go towards the entrance, as if it were trying to discourage them. The level turns dark, sound becomes muffled, clouds disappear, the floor rumbles, and hallucinations kick in. There are writings on the walls, presumably by other wanderers, which read "YOU WILL REGRET THIS," "Don't you want to know?" and "Please don't leave me," among others. Many of these writings seem to oppose one another. There is not much documentation on people who have gotten close to the door; presumably, those who enter the door disappear.

{{Blurimage|align=right|hovertext=This is what happened.|file=This is what happened..jpg|caption=<big>This is what happened.</big>

<small>A presumed image of the forest.</small>}}

It is unknown what is outside the boundaries of the level. Many believe it is [[the Void]] or even an exit to another level. However, some claim that outside the borders is a big rainforest. It is theorized that there is a white door somewhere in it, connected by threads and poles, forming the boundary of a house that is similar in shape to the one in the level's center.

There is a comet in the sky of '''Level 365''' known as the Lucid Comet. It is a giant, white comet with a long tail. Around the comet, the sky appears to turn darker, and clouds get further away from it. Researchers say the comet passes through '''Level 365''' every year, inching closer to the surface as time passes.{{Blurimage|align=right|caption=<big>It's coming.</big>

<small>A picture of the Lucid Comet.</small>|hovertext=Lucid Comet|file=Lucid Comet 2.jpg}}
<br>Several timers are commonly found throughout the level, namely, calendars that mark themselves as days pass. All time-counting objects in '''Level 365''' display the same time, independent of how they are configured. Any item as such will begin counting time anomalously once it enters the level. These all seem to count down to the day the Lucid Comet will hit the level.

A prolonged stay on '''Level 365''' will cause one to experience the "Lobotomy Effect." Early symptoms include shorter attention spans, hallucinations, and loss of bodily autonomy. The effect becomes noticeable and passes more slowly as it becomes stronger. However, it can be diminished through mental training, meditation, and physical tasks. If the effect goes on for too long, it will eventually become irreversible, even through medical procedures or mental training.

==Living Organisms==
There is no life present in '''Level 365''', other than wanderers that enter the level and the plants. 

==Human Settlements==
Due to '''Level 365'''<nowiki/>'s nature and properties, no settlements can be established within it. As aforementioned, wanderers are kicked out of the level when another person arrives.

